Description: Annunciation, with Virgin sitting under open vestibule supported by four pillars, and angel appearing on the left Etching
Curator's comments: Plate 1 from a series of six etchings depicting the life of the Virgin, from the Annunciation to the flight into Egypt.
Acquisition notes: R,8.119 to 142 is a uniform group of 24 etchings by Mauperché, of similar fine quality, presentation and provenance. But not one of them gives any indication of their provenance on the verso. Given their relationship to the contemporary landscapes by Swanevelt, of which Cracherode possessed a fine group, one would expect that they all came from him, and may have been extracted from a small album in his library (which would explain the absence of markings). This is far more plausible than a Courten/Sloane provenance, but cannot be proven.(AVG)
